cs.CL, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on semantic parsing of natural language commands for service robots. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper specifically mentions the RoboCup@Home General Purpose Service Robot task and evaluates the proposed approach in that context. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper proposes a method that leverages neural semantic parsing methods to enable the training of a semantic parser with little data and without domain specific parser engineering. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is also possible as the paper uses contextual word embeddings and neural networks for semantic parsing. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a neural semantic parsing approach.
